# Kongsian WA Tunnel — runtime config

**Set on the deployed Worker (kongsian-api-dev):**
```
# From the apps/api directory
wrangler secret put WA_PROVIDER_URL --env dev
# paste: https://tool-nominations-pine-pixel.trycloudflare.com

wrangler secret put WA_PROVIDER_SECRET --env dev
# paste the contents of /root/kongsian/.wa-relay-secret
```

**What's running on this VPS:**
| Process | Port | Purpose | Auto-restart? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Hermes WhatsApp bridge | 127.0.0.1:3000 | Already running, scanned QR, scans messages | yes (whatsapp-watchdog.sh, */5 cron) |
| wa-relay.ts | 0.0.0.0:3031 | Bridges Worker HTTP calls to Hermes bridge format | NO — manual restart if this box reboots |
| cloudflared quick tunnel | outbound to Cloudflare edge | Exposes 3031 as trycloudflare URL | NO — manual restart |

**Tunnel URL:** https://tool-nominations-pine-pixel.trycloudflare.com
This URL is **stable for the current cloudflared session only** — restart cloudflared and the URL changes. The secret in WA_PROVIDER_SECRET is stable.

**Logs:**
- wa-relay: /root/kongsian/.wa-relay.log
- cloudflared: /root/kongsian/.cloudflared.log

**To restart wa-relay after a reboot** (run as root):
```bash
cd /root/kongsian
# Read the secret into a shell var, then exec the relay. Do this with source
# (set -a exports every var assignment) so the secret never appears in
# ps output. The wa-relay.sh wrapper script below does this.
bash /root/kongsian/scripts/start-wa-relay.sh > /root/kongsian/.wa-relay.log 2>&1 &
```

The wrapper script /root/kongsian/scripts/start-wa-relay.sh reads the secret
from /root/kongsian/.wa-relay-secret and execs wa-relay.ts. Check that the
script reads correctly:
```bash
cat /root/kongsian/scripts/start-wa-relay.sh
# Should NOT contain any $() command substitution (those got redacted on
# first write — fall back to manual launch below if it's broken).
```

**Manual fallback** (if start-wa-relay.sh is broken, paste the secret inline):
```bash
cd /root/kongsian
SECRET=*** /root/kongsian/.wa-relay-secret)
export WA_RELAY_PORT=3031
export WA_BRIDGE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000
/root/kongsian/packages/db/node_modules/.bin/tsx /root/kongsian/scripts/wa-relay.ts
```

**To restart cloudflared after a reboot:**
```bash
cloudflared tunnel --no-autoupdate --url http://localhost:3031 > /root/kongsian/.cloudflared.log 2>&1 &
# After ~5s, the new trycloudflare URL is in the log:
grep -E 'trycloudflare.com.*\|' /root/kongsian/.cloudflared.log
# Update WA_PROVIDER_URL on the Worker to the new URL.
```

**To upgrade to a stable URL** (recommended before wife does the real trial):
A Cloudflare Named Tunnel gives a fixed URL like wa.kongsian.app that survives
restarts. Needs a Cloudflare account with kongsian.app on Cloudflare DNS, which
is on hold until you decide whether to buy the domain. Skip for now.
